        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 1:12PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 111 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Sacramento, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Timberon, Sacramento, Weed, Hay Canyon, Avis, and Surveyors Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
